  85:mi/plaits/dsp/engine2/wave_terrain_engine.cpp **** // The wavetables are stored in integrated form. Either we directly use the
  86:mi/plaits/dsp/engine2/wave_terrain_engine.cpp **** // integrated data (which can have large variations in amplitude), or we
  87:mi/plaits/dsp/engine2/wave_terrain_engine.cpp **** // differentiate it on the fly to recover the original waveform. This second
  88:mi/plaits/dsp/engine2/wave_terrain_engine.cpp **** // option can be noisier, and it would ideally need a low pass-filter.
  89:mi/plaits/dsp/engine2/wave_terrain_engine.cpp **** 
  90:mi/plaits/dsp/engine2/wave_terrain_engine.cpp **** #define DIFFERENTIATE_WAVE_DATA
  91:mi/plaits/dsp/engine2/wave_terrain_engine.cpp **** 
